data.enText: door/gate
a door, gate, passage, etc. used for entering a room, building or place
the entrance to the museum/the museum entrance

data.chText: 房子的前门 / 后门 / 侧门
data.enText: the front/back/side entrance of the house

data.chText: 灯塔是进入海港航道的标志。
data.enText: A lighthouse marks the entrance to the harbour.
an entrance hall/lobby
I'll meet you at the main entrance .
going in
the act of entering a room, building or place, especially in a way that attracts the attention of other people

data.chText: 他的突然出场使所有人都感到意外。
data.enText: His sudden entrance took everyone by surprise.

data.chText: 响亮的喇叭声是国王驾到的信号。
data.enText: A fanfare signalled the entrance of the king.

data.chText: 她在其他所有客人都到达后才入场。
data.enText: She made her entrance after all the other guests had arrived.
The hero makes his entrance (= walks onto the stage) in Scene 2.
the right or opportunity to enter a building or place

data.chText: 他们被拒于展览会门外。
data.enText: They were refused entrance to the exhibition.
an entrance fee (= money paid to go into a museum, etc.)

data.chText: 警方怎么也进不去这栋房子。
data.enText: The police were unable to gain entrance to the house.
becoming involved
the act of becoming involved in sth

data.chText: 这家公司戏剧性地打入了出口市场。
data.enText: The company made a dramatic entrance into the export market.
to club/institution

data.chText: （俱乐部、社团、大学等的）准许加入，进入许可
data.enText: permission to become a member of a club, society, university, etc.
a university entrance exam
entrance requirements

data.chText: 只有有人担保才能加入这个高尔夫俱乐部。
data.enText: Entrance to the golf club is by sponsorship only.
to make sb feel great pleasure and admiration so that they give sb/sth all their attention

data.chText: 他听她讲话听得出了神。
data.enText: He listened to her, entranced.
entrancing music

ex.chText: 我们在入口处排队参观展览。
ex.enText: We queued up at the entrance for the exhibition.

synonyms.bx: 含义广泛，作“进入”解时，尤指以被人们注意到的方式；作“入口”解时，一般指有门或围栏的入口处。

ex.chText: 大楼唯一的入口被堵住了。
ex.enText: The only access to the building was blocked.
Access to the restrooms is through the hall.

synonyms.bx: 指进入建筑物或到达某处的通道，常后接介词 to。

ex.chText: 我会在游乐园入口处等你。
ex.enText: I'll wait for you at the entry to the amusement park.

ex.chText: 我们可以把伞放在入口处。
ex.enText: We can leave our umbrellas at the entry.

ex.chText: 洞穴的入口被树丛遮掩着。
ex.enText: The entry to the cave was hidden by trees.

ex.chText: 在博物馆的入口处发现了一枚炸弹。
ex.enText: A bomb was found at the entry to the museum.

synonyms.bx: 指某一场所（如建筑物、大厅等）的入口处或进入的通道。

tr: something that provides access (to get in or get out)
example: they waited at the entrance to the garden
beggars waited just outside the entryway to the cathedral
She captured all the men's hearts

value.def: The entrance to a place is the way into it, for example a door or gate.

example.ex: Beside the entrance to the church, turn right...
He was driven out of a side entrance with his hand covering his face...
example.tran: 他被从侧门赶了出来，一只手还捂着脸。

example.ex: A marble entrance hall leads to a sitting room.
example.tran: 大理石门厅通往起居室。

value.def: You can refer to someone's arrival in a place as their entrance, especially when you think that they are trying to be noticed and admired.

example.ex: If she had noticed her father's entrance, she gave no indication.
example.tran: 就算她已经注意到了父亲的到来，她也会不动声色。

value.tran: 到达;（尤指有意引人注目的）驾到，莅临

value.def: When a performer makes his or her entrance on to the stage, he or she comes on to the stage.

example.ex: He made his entrance into the parade ring.

gramarinfo.label: usu sing, usu with poss, oft N <l>on/into</l> n

value.def: If you gain entrance to a particular place, you manage to get in there.

example.ex: Hewitt had gained entrance to the Hall by pretending to be a heating engineer.
example.tran: 休伊特装扮成供热工程师从而进入大厅。

value.def: If you gain entrance to a particular profession, society, or institution, you are accepted as a member of it.

example.ex: Entrance to universities and senior secondary schools was restricted.
example.tran: 进入大学或高中的资格受到限制。

example.ex: ...entrance exams for the French civil service.

value.tran: 入会资格;入学资格;入行资格

value.def: If you make an entrance into a particular activity or system, you succeed in becoming involved in it.

example.ex: The acquisition helped BCCI make its initial entrance into the US market.
example.tran: 那项并购帮助国际商业信贷银行首次跻身美国市场。

value.def: If something or someone entrances you, they cause you to feel delight and wonder, often so that all your attention is taken up and you cannot think about anything else.

example.ex: As soon as I met Dick, he entranced me because he has a lovely voice...
example.tran: 我一遇到迪克，就被他那动听的声音迷住了。

example.ex: Last Friday she entranced the audience with her classical Indian singing.
example.tran: 上周五她演唱的经典印度歌曲让听众如痴如醉。

example.ex: I became entranced with the idea...
For the next three hours we sat entranced as the train made its way up the mountains...
example.tran: 在接下来的3个小时里，随着火车缘山而上，我们坐在座位上陶醉于周围的景致。

example.ex: He is entranced by the kindness of her smile.
example.tran: 他被她和善的微笑迷住了。

example.ex: The light reflected off the stone, creating a golden glow he found entrancing.
example.tran: 钻石折射出的金色光芒令他着迷。
